    author: "On The Go Moving Team",
    heroImage: BRAND_IMAGES.truckBellevueSkyline,
    intro: `If you are considering moving to West Bellevue and want to know what it’s like before making the final relocation decision, this article is for you. There are a number of reasons why you might choose to live in West Bellevue instead of Downtown Bellevue or Seattle.`,
    sections: [
      { type: "h2", heading: `Living In West Bellevue`, body: `What are the benefits and negatives of living in West Bellevue? Let’s take a look at the various things that you should consider as someone who is planning a move to West Bellevue . And to kick things off, let’s talk about population size. While the population of Bellevue itself is 144,403, West Bellevue has a more modest number of residents — 17,227 to be exact. Despite the relatively small community size, a move to West Bellevue is almost certain to prove a wise career move for you. Being a neighbor to both Seattle and Bellevue, it’s only natural that West Bellevue’s job market is also...` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Cost of Living In West Bellevue`, body: `What is the cost of living in West Bellevue? It’s no secret that the cost of living in West Bellevue is significantly higher than the Washington State average. If you are comparing cost of living in Seattle versus Bellevue, you’ll find that the cost of living is pretty much the same between the two, with groceries, transportation, and dining out, running you about the same in each city.` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Bellevue West Apartments`, body: `When it comes to West Bellevue real estate and apartment costs, you will find yourself facing some pretty impressive numbers. The average cost of rent in West Bellevue is around $2,100, while the average cost of buying a house is hovering just around the million-dollar mark. This places both renting and buying well above the national average and well over Washington State’s averages for both.` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Living In West Bellevue Things To Do`, body: `When it comes to West Bellevue things to do, there is no shortage of activities to suit anyone from any walk of life. If you’re fond of day trips, check out nearby Mount Rainier National Park , or if you want to explore a Bavarian settlement, take a drive to Leavenworth . If, however, you’re in the mood for something local, keep reading to find your next West Bellevue activity.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `Best Bars In West Bellevue, WA`, body: `If you’re fond of classy, retro, or trendy bar scenes, Bellevue WA will have something for you. Three of our top picks for the best bars in West Bellevue, WA include: Paddy Coyne’s Irish Pub W Living Room Bar Central Bar + Restaurant` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `West Bellevue Shopping`, body: `If you’re a fan of urban shopping scenes, Bellevue can accommodate you there as well. Some of the best shopping to be found in Bellevue include: Bellevue Square The Shops At The Bravern` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `Best Restaurants in West Bellevue, WA`, body: `Whether you’re looking for a pizza house in West Bellevue or the best sushi, here are some of West Bellevue’s greatest restaurants. Bis on Main Pearl Seafood & Oyster Bar Duke’s Seafood John Howie Steak Cantinetta Bellevue Japonessa` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `Related Articles`, body: `Fun Things To Do In Bellevue Parks & Water Recreation Park Bellevue Living in Queen Anne Seattle Living In West Seattle, WA Living on Mercer Island` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Bellevue West High School & Education`, body: `If you’re a parent considering a move to West Bellevue, you’ll be very satisfied with what the public education system has to offer. According to Niche.com, West Bellevue scores an A+ for public schooling as well as an A+ for family life. Moving to West Bellevue will ensure that your children have multiple opportunities in the educational sphere and will surround you with other like-minded families.` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Moving To West Bellevue, WA`, body: `If you’re planning a relocation to West Bellevue in the near future, make your move easier by enlisting the helpful assistance of a relocation service. Here at On The Go Moving, we provide quality relocation services to ensure that each of our clients has the easiest transition into their new home city as possible. We believe in helping take some of the burden off of your shoulders and we like to do this by matching our moving services to meet your exact needs. Reasons in Moving to Bellevue, WA The majestic city of Bellevue is located 15 miles east of Seattle, Washington, and has… Everything...` }
    ],
