      { type: "h2", heading: `Parks In Sammamish WA`, body: `If you’re a lover of the outdoors, the parks in Sammamish WA will be more than enough to satisfy your love of nature. Some of the best parks in Sammamish WA include: Sammamish Landing Park Sammamish Commons Park Beaver Lake & Preserve` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Sammamish Events`, body: `Community is a huge part of Sammamish culture and life, so if you’re looking for a community to get involved with, you’ll fit right in as a Sammamish resident. Annual Sammamish events include: Sammamish Farmers Market. The Sammamish Farmers Market is held every Wednesday (May to September) from 4pm to 8pm. Fourth on the Plateau. Sammamish’s Fourth on the Plateau event is held every Fourth Of July from 6pm to 10:30 pm. Nightmare at Beaver Lake. The Nightmare at Beaver Lake is an annual event held at the end of October to celebrate Halloween. If you love the spooky autumn season, you should...` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `Related Articles`, body: `Things To Do In Everett Things To Do in Seattle in Winter Fun Things to Do in Bothell Best Things to Do in Redmond` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Moving To Sammamish Soon?`, body: `If you’re relocating to Sammamish in the near future, give yourself the gift that you deserve by hiring a Sammamish moving company to help you complete your move with as little stress as possible. Here at On The Go Moving , we offer a variety of different moving services to accommodate the needs of all of our clients. If you need help with packing, storage, transportation, or lifting, give us a call at 425-441-3390 to speak with one of our Sammamish movers . We’d be happy to flush out a moving plan with you or discuss pricing in order to help you feel more comfortable and confident during...` }
