  "things-to-do-in-kirkland-wa": {
    slug: "things-to-do-in-kirkland-wa",
    title: `Things to Do in Kirkland, WA`,
    metaTitle: `Things to Do in Kirkland, WA | On The Go Moving`,
    metaDescription: `Looking for things to do in Kirkland, WA? Explore waterfront parks, dining, shopping, outdoor activities, and local attractions for all ages.`,
    date: "October 1, 2020",
    dateISO: "2020-10-01",
    category: "Local Guides",
    readTime: "4 min read",
    author: "On The Go Moving Team",
    heroImage: BRAND_IMAGES.truckKirklandHouse,
    intro: `Moving to Kirkland in the near future and looking for fun things to do there? You’re in luck! Kirkland is home to gorgeous parks, delightful waterfront restaurants, and activities aplenty. Whether you’re moving to Kirkland solo, with your partner, or with a family, you will never lack for fun things to do in this vibrant city.`,
    sections: [
      { type: "h3", heading: `Related Article`, body: `Living in Kirkland, WA Fun Things to Do in Bothell Things To Do In Everett Things To Do in Seattle in Winter Best Things to Do in Redmond` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Fun Things To Do in Kirkland Washington`, body: `As Kirkland’s go-to moving experts, we have a lot of experience driving around this city. Here are some of our favorite things to do whenever we have a day off in town:` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `1) Visit a Winery`, body: `Washington State is well known for its wineries and artisan wine production. And while many of Washington’s best wineries are in Eastern Washington, Kirkland also holds claim to being home to several fine wineries. One excellent option is Northwest Cellars, where you’ll be treated to some of Washington’s finest wines. Northwest Cellars is the perfect place to treat yourself, your partner, or your group of friends. Schedule a visit so that you can sit back and enjoy the best wines Washington has to offer, served in a relaxed environment.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `2) Cross Kirkland Corridor`, body: `Another fun thing to do in Kirkland, Washington is to take a walk along the Cross Kirkland Corridor. The Cross Kirkland Corridor is a nearly six-mile-long trail that winds through the heart of the city. You can enjoy jogging, biking, or walking the trail with friends, your partner, or your dog! This lovely nature trail gives Kirkland residents a quiet escape from the city and is a great way to breathe in the fresh air while getting a bit of exercise.` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Explore Kirkland’s Waterfront and Parks`, body: `Kirkland is widely known for its scenic waterfront along Lake Washington. Residents and visitors alike enjoy walking paths, open green spaces, and waterfront views that make the area ideal for relaxing or staying active. Many parks in Kirkland are easily accessible from downtown, allowing people to enjoy the outdoors without traveling far. The combination of lake access and well-maintained public spaces is a defining feature of the city.` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Waterfront Restaurants in Kirkland Washington`, body: `The city of Kirkland, Washington has an undeniably gorgeous waterfront. It’s laid out on the cusp of Lake Washington, giving Kirkland residents access to the waterfront as well as a host of lovely restaurants. Some of Kirkland’s best waterfront restaurants include:` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `3) Anthony’s HomePort Kirkland`, body: `With gorgeous waterfront views, Anthony’s HomePort is the perfect place for a romantic dinner for two. Serving fresh, locally sourced seafood and a selection of regional wines and beers, guests at Anthony’s HomePort can taste the Puget Sound freshness in each bite.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `4) BeachHouse Bar + Grill`, body: `For a more casual waterfront restaurant experience, visit BeachHouse Bar + Grill. At BeachHouse Bar + Grill, you are greeted by a vast menu with dishes ranging from grilled steak salads, local seafood dishes, authentic pasta, and hearty burgers. If you are looking for a cozy, waterfront restaurant in Kirkland, Washington, head on over to BeachHouse Bar + Grill.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `5) Le Grand Bistro Americain`, body: `In the mood for French food? Visit Le Grand Bistro Americain for mouth-watering creme brulee, escargots bourguignon, or charcuterie. Le Grand Bistro Americain is a waterfront restaurant with a relaxed atmosphere and quintessentially French menu. Make a reservation for this weekend to enjoy the best French food and waterfront views that Kirkland has to offer.` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Parks in Kirkland Washington`, body: `Here are a couple of Kirkland, Washington’s best parks. If you’re looking for the perfect picnicking spot for this weekend, hop in your car and take a drive down to one of these parks. Marina Park has it all, boat mooring, picnic tables, fishing access, and an outdoor amphitheater. It’s the perfect place for a sunset picnic or a stroll along Lake Washington. You can soak in the perfect ambiance of nature with your friends or family and watch the lake lap lazily at the shore.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `7) Juanita Bay Park`, body: `Another Kirkland park that is worth a visit is Juanita Bay Park. With more than 100-acres dedicated to native foliage and habitat preservation, Juanita Bay Park is the perfect place to bask in undisturbed nature. If you have kids, Juanita Bay Park is the perfect place to go in search of wildlife or for an afternoon of bird watching.` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Outdoor Activities and Recreation in Kirkland`, body: `Outdoor recreation is a major part of life in Kirkland. The city offers opportunities for walking, biking, paddleboarding, and casual sports throughout the year. Trails and parks support both leisurely outings and more active routines, making Kirkland appealing to people who enjoy spending time outside. Seasonal changes also bring variety, from summer lake activities to peaceful waterfront walks in cooler months.` }
    ],
    faqs: [],
    relatedService: "Residential Moving",
    relatedServiceHref: "/residential-moving/"
  },
