    title: `How to Protect Fragile Items During a Move`,
    metaTitle: `How to Protect Fragile Items During a Move | On The Go Moving`,
    metaDescription: `Learn how to pack fragile items for moving safely. Get expert advice on protecting glass during a move and preventing damage with smart packing techniques.`,
    date: "December 20, 2024",
    dateISO: "2024-12-20",
    category: "Moving Tips",
    readTime: "3 min read",
    author: "On The Go Moving Team",
    heroImage: BRAND_IMAGES.crewWrappingFurniture,
    intro: `Learn how to pack fragile items for moving with proper padding and wrapping techniques. Use dividers and vertical packing to protect glass during a move. Avoid overloading boxes and fill gaps to keep fragile items secure. Double-box delicate items for the best way to move fragile items safely. Moving can be stressful—especially when fragile items are involved. Whether it’s delicate glassware, heirloom dishes, or prized electronics, how to pack fragile items for moving is an art that requires...`,
    sections: [
      { type: "h2", heading: `Packing Fragile Items Tips to Prevent Damage`, body: `These additional packing fragile items tips can make all the difference: Fill in Gaps: Empty spaces inside the box can cause items to shift during transit. Use crumpled paper or packing peanuts to fill every gap. Pack Electronics Carefully: For TVs, monitors, and other electronics, use original packaging if available. If not, wrap screens in blankets or foam and secure them with straps. Avoid Overloading Boxes: Heavy boxes are harder to handle and more likely to be dropped. Keep boxes light enough to carry comfortably. Double Box Delicate Items: For extra protection, place fragile items in a...` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Protecting Glass During a Move`, body: `Protecting glass during a move takes a bit more care, but it’s worth it to keep your mirrors, vases, and glassware safe: Use Glass-Safe Wrapping: Wrap glass items in foam sheets or bubble wrap, and secure them with tape to prevent shifting. Place Plates and Glasses Vertically: Pack plates and glasses on their sides instead of stacking them flat—this reduces the chances of breakage from top-down pressure. Add Cushioning Between Layers: When packing multiple layers of glassware in one box, use soft materials like towels or blankets between each layer for added protection.` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Make Your Move Stress-Free with On the Go Moving`, body: `Packing Fragile Items Prior to Moving Dealing with a fragile package is one of the most anxiety-inducing parts of moving. Few… Benefits of Using Professional Warehousing Services During Your Move - Professional warehousing services offer secure, climate-controlled storage solutions to protect your belongings from theft,… 10 Tips: Things Most Families Forget During a Move Moving is a big and stressful event, made even more stressful when you are trying… Dealing with a fragile package is one of the most anxiety-inducing parts of moving. Few… - Professional warehousing services offer secure,...` }
    ],
    faqs: [],
