    author: "On The Go Moving Team",
    heroImage: BRAND_IMAGES.truckResidentialStreet,
    intro: `Enjoy a true taste of Washington by visiting the best restaurants in Redmond, WA. Whether you have a hankering for some comfort food, a gourmet meal, or sizzling street treats, the city offers you a wide variety of dining options. Our team at On The Go Moving & Storage knows which places you should try first. Our thriving city enjoys a rich supply of organic produce and fresh catches. The food in Redmond mirrors the city’s diverse culture. Aside from the standard American cuisine, locals and...`,
    sections: [
      { type: "h2", heading: `Redmond Restaurants`, body: `Please your palate by discovering the best places to eat in Redmond. Moving to a new town can prove daunting on its own. Once you arrive, not knowing where to eat can sometimes add to the stress. To ease the acclimation process after landing in Redmond, we compiled a list of the best restaurants in Redmond, WA. See which one whets your appetite the most. What began as an eatery at Overlake Park for Thai Airways crew members in 1989 soon became all the rage for Redmond locals. Bai Tong's aromatic rice preparations demand the spotlight. Top dishes include crispy garlic chicken, seafood noodles,...` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `Sages Restaurant`, body: `One of the best downtown Redmond restaurants, Sages serves Italian and European food. A review of its various offerings would remain incomplete without mentioning its curated wine list that contains some of the best bottles from local wineries. Customers can also savor tasty options from a separate, gluten-free menu section. The most popular dishes include Bart’s clam chowder, Bart’s signature chicken, and pork tenderloin.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `Tipsy Cow Burger Bar`, body: `Satisfy your hamburger habit at Tipsy Cow Burger Bar on Cleveland Street. The classic Tipsy Burger stands out for its fresh, artisanal Macrina Bakery buns. This unique menu features their signature dipping sauce, Tipsy Gold fries, and burger add-ons. Some of the bestselling burgers include Beast Mode, Thai Fighter, Fry Subs, and The Experience. Enjoy rich, rustic flavors at this popular Italian restaurant in Redmond. Blu Sardinia’s menu gets its inspiration from the Old Country and features authentic Italian food infused with the flavors of the Pacific Northwest. You can try the famous...` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Redmond’s Best Restaurants`, body: `Kanishka stands out for having the most diverse menu among Redmond restaurants that serve Indian cuisine. Taste the spices of India in the chef’s exotic preparations. You will find classic Indian treats like samosas, paneer makhani, and a variety of spicy chicken and lamb preparations. Treat yourself to a refreshing glass of lassi, a traditional Indian drink made from yogurt and milk infused with seasonings.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `Pomegranate Bistro`, body: `Many customers stop by this restaurant for the best breakfast in Redmond. The bistro stands out for its Southern-style comfort food and cocktails. The cafe and bakery serve as an ideal family hangout for a light-hearted meal. They serve traditional American dishes consisting of toast and waffles, sandwiches, salads, and a wide range of beverages.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `The Stone House`, body: `This Redmond dining option on Cleveland Street, also known as The Wiley House, boasts a marvelous ambiance for fine dining. The Stone House’s exquisite architecture dates back to the early 1900s, featuring a comfortable seating area where you can host a formal dinner or throw a fancy birthday bash. The menu’s delectable seafood dishes remain a customer favorite. The culinary team changes it based on the availability of fresh ingredients.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `Related Articles`, body: `Best Things to Do in Redmond Redmond Parks` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Best Restaurants to Satisfy Your Cravings!`, body: `At On The Go Moving & Storage, we know that food plays a central role in Redmond’s vibrant community life. We hand-picked the restaurants on our list to satisfy your food cravings as well as your adventurous spirit. Immerse yourself in our city’s diverse culture by checking out the most delectable restaurants in Redmond, WA. Find the favorite hangouts for Redmond’s early risers, happy hour crowds, and night owls. Have you found your next home or office in Redmond, WA? Our professional movers at On The Go Moving & Storage ensure safe passage and a soft landing for your belongings. Call us at...` }
    ],
