      { type: "h2", heading: `What To Do in Redmond Washington`, body: `Here are 20 of the top things to do in Redmond, Washington. This list includes Redmond attractions, places of interest to visit in Redmond, and fun weekend suggestions.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `1. Evans Creek Preserve — Nature Trails & Wildlife`, body: `Evans Creek Preserve lets you experience Redmond’s natural landscapes with: Gentle nature trails Wetlands, forests, and open spaces Great spots for picnicking and bird watching Gentle nature trails Wetlands, forests, and open spaces Great spots for picnicking and bird watching It’s a peaceful alternative to larger parks and ideal for a family day out. This nature preserve offers more than 200 acres of forest, meadows, and wetlands to explore. The Preserve makes for a fun and educational thing to do in Redmond with kids as there’s plenty of space to play and an abundance of animal wildlife to...` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `2. Cave B Estate Winery`, body: `If you are passionate about artisan wine and wine tasting, Redmond has several wineries that are sure to interest you. One of the best wineries to visit on the weekend is Cave B Estate Winery . Here you may get a taste of some of Washington’s finest wine in a relaxed atmosphere. Whether you’re looking for a relaxing solo activity, or a place for a get together with friends on the weekend, visit Cave B Estate Winery.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `3. Flee Escape Room`, body: `If you enjoy thrilling hobbies, visit Flee Escape Room in Redmond . Flee Escape room is one of the most fun ways to spend a birthday or plan a team-building activity in Redmond. For the true crime, problem-solving Redmond geniuses, an escape room is one of Redmond’s most fun things to do during a free weekend. Plan your next Redmond activity with Flee Escape Room today for a Sherlock Holmes, crime-junkie experience.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `4. Redmond Bike Park`, body: `If you enjoy dirt biking and adrenaline-inducing jumps, Redmond Bike Park is going to become a local haunt for you. This is a local Redmond activity for bikers and outdoor sports enthusiasts alike and is sure to introduce you to a group of cool Redmonders.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `5. Sammamish River Trail — Scenic Walks & Biking`, body: `The Sammamish River Trail is one of the region’s most popular paths for: Cycling and jogging Leisurely walks along the river Wildlife viewing and nature photography Cycling and jogging Leisurely walks along the river Wildlife viewing and nature photography Stretching for miles, this trail connects Redmond to neighboring communities and is ideal for outdoor exploration. A gorgeous trail running more than ten miles alongside the Sammamish River, Sammamish River Trail provides a tranquil natural environment for joggers and nature lovers. The trail offers a fun thing to do during a weekend in...` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `6. Eastside Symphony`, body: `Passionate about the orchestra and local talent? Eastside Symphony is a community orchestra that provides Redmond with the delightful classical symphony as well as lesser-known pieces. If you are a symphony enthusiast, Eastside Symphony will be one of your favorite Redmond activities.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `7. Marymoor Park — Outdoor Recreation Hub`, body: `If outdoor recreation is your hobby, Marymoor Park will charm you. With more than 600-acres of green space, soccer, baseball, and cricket grounds, this park is the perfect place to spend a weekend in Redmond. If you prefer a more relaxing Redmond activity, Marymoor Park is also the perfect picnicking and bird-watching spot in Redmond. Marymoor Park is Redmond’s most visited and iconic destination. Spanning over 640 acres, this park features: Walking and biking trails Velodrome and rock climbing A 40-acre off-leash dog area Concerts and community events in summer Scenic picnic and play areas...` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `8. Postdoc Brewing`, body: `Looking for a pup-friendly, kid-friendly brewery with some of the best local beer? Postdoc Brewing started out as a small passion project in a family’s garage but quickly grew to be one of Redmond’s most popular breweries. The relaxed atmosphere, a wide selection of craft beers, and rotating food trucks make Postdoc Brewing a perfect weekend activity for Redmond residents.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `9. SecondStory Repertory`, body: `In search of weekend entertainment options in Redmond? One of the top Redmond weekend activities is a visit to SecondStory Repertory . Here you can be entertained by local talent including actors, comedians, and musicians. If you enjoy live entertainment and want to support local performers, a visit SecondStory Repertory this weekend is well worth your time.` }
