    title: `Parks In Bellevue WA | Water Recreation, Park Near Bellevue Square`,
    metaTitle: `Parks In Bellevue WA | Water Recreation, Park Near... | On The Go Moving`,
    metaDescription: `Bellevue is known for having some beautiful parks. Form lushish green to refreshing water, check out the top 7 parks to visit in the Bellevue area!`,
    date: "July 11, 2020",
    dateISO: "2020-07-11",
    category: "Local Guides",
    readTime: "4 min read",
    author: "On The Go Moving Team",
    heroImage: BRAND_IMAGES.truckBellevueSkyline,
    intro: `If you are considering relocating to Bellevue, Washington , in the near future then Bellevue movers are the best moving services in the area for the convenient relocation to the city. Bellevue is the best place for you if you're looking to live around plenty of green spaces within the city. Here is a list of some of the best parks in Bellevue. Whether you have a dog and are looking for dog-friendly parks, or family-friendly, recreational parks, Bellevue has green spaces aplenty with activities...`,
    sections: [
      { type: "h3", heading: `Related Article`, body: `Living in Bellevue Redmond Parks Rest assured that relocating to Bellevue Washington in no way means that you will be trapped in a concrete jungle — on the contrary, Bellevue has a lot of diverse parks both in the city and nearby.` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `7 Top Bellevue Parks To Visit In 2020`, body: `Without further ado, here is a list of the 7 best parks in Bellevue Washington.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `1. Bellevue Downtown Park`, body: `A central green space in Bellevue, Downtown Park is the perfect location for walking your dog on warm Washington mornings, having a picnic and several volleyball games with friends, going for a morning jog, or just relaxing on a bench while letting your kids play on the playground. Downtown Park is located with skyscrapers all around and offers a serene escape for Bellevue residents during lunch break or after a long workday.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `2. Bellevue Botanical Garden`, body: `A visit to Bellevue Botanical Garden will make you feel that you’ve stepped into another world. Bursting with verdant woodlands and wetlands, Bellevue Botanical Garden has its very own Japanese garden as well as wetlands and woodlands throughout the park. Visit during the summer for outdoor concerts or in the winter to catch the park festively lit with holiday lights. This is one of the best parks in Bellevue to disconnect and relax in a peaceful, elven-like environment.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `3. Meydenbauer Bay Park`, body: `If you’re looking for a park in Bellevue, Washington with water access, Meydenbauer Bay Park is the place to go. You can rent kayaks and paddle around the park bay, watch the sunset peacefully over the water, or visit the park on a weekend for a family picnic. This Bellevue park has a water area for swimming as well as a playground, so it’s a wonderful park for the whole family.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `4. Enatai Beach Park`, body: `Another wonderful Bellevue park with water and recreation activities is Enatai Beach Park . You can rent kayaks, canoes, or paddleboards, relax in the picnic area, or swim in the lake to cool off. This is the perfect Bellevue park for the whole family and is a great place to spend a summer afternoon with family and friends with a picnic lunch. Related Article: Things To Do in Bellevue WA` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `5. Clyde Beach Park`, body: `This is the perfect park in Bellevue, Washington to bring your dog for an afternoon of fun. Clyde Beach Park has a small play and recreation area for kids and picnic tables, as well as a dock and swimming area. This beautiful Bellevue Park is conveniently located within walking distance of downtown Bellevue and offers a peaceful escape for employees to visit during lunch break or after work.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `6. Wilburton Hill Park`, body: `If you are looking for a Bellevue park that has all of the recreational activities in one place, visit Wilburton Hill Park . At this wonderful recreational Bellevue park you will find wooded play and picnic areas, walking trails aplenty, soccer and baseball fields, and even a mini zip-line. Wilburton Hill Park is a great place to walk your dog or go for a morning jog. If you are into exercising and fitness, this Bellevue park even has adult exercising equipment that you can use.` },
      { type: "h3", heading: `7. Newcastle Beach Park`, body: `If you are looking for a family gathering place, Bellevue’s Newcastle Beach Park is the best spot. This park in Bellevue has covered barbecues and picnic tables for grilling on a summer weekend. Newcastle Beach Park also has lake access where you can swim or do water recreational activities.` },
      { type: "h2", heading: `Moving to Bellevue Soon?`, body: `If you are planning a move to Bellevue, Washington in the near future, congratulations! Bellevue is a wonderful place to live with plenty of parks and green spaces for every type of Bellevue resident. If you need help with your upcoming move, give On The Go Moving a call today. We use our professional moving and Bellevue storage services to help those relocating to the Bellevue area have a stress-free move. To hear more about our different moving plans and packages, give us a call today . Parks Near Downtown Seattle, WA If you want to escape from downtown Seattle’s hustle and bustle, you're...` }
    ],
